cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on building and training self-replicating neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential benefits of self-replication for artificial intelligence, which could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a loss function and optimization methods is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The concept of natural selection and continual improvement could be considered under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the design of a self-replicating neural network that can solve an auxiliary task such as image classification could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
